02/05/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Thousands gathered in Athens on Sunday (May 1st) to mark Labour Day, demanding a better life amid the government's ongoing austerity reforms. Similar demonstrations were held in Thessaloniki, Patra and the island of Crete. Train and ferry workers marked the day with a strike. In a public address, Prime Minister George Papandreou acknowledged that Greeks are leading a battle for survival, and that this year finds Greece in its deepest crisis ever. (Imerisia - 02/05/11; Xinhua, ERT, Ta Nea, Kathimerini - 01/05/11)
